Package songsorter.python

Class PythonEnvHandler

java.lang.Object
songsorter.python.PythonEnvHandler
public class PythonEnvHandler extends Object
Class to handle all Python based tasks within a virtual environment that works from the Caches folder on MacOS only

  • Constructor Details

    • PythonEnvHandler

      public PythonEnvHandler() throws PythonError, InterruptedException, IOException
      Creates a Python environment and installs all python dependencies via Pip.

      Note: This process can be intensive and may take some time

      Throws:
      PythonError - if Python is not installed on the user's system.
      IOException - If reading/writing to CLI fails
      InterruptedException - If underlying Python script fails mid-execution

    • runCommand

      public String runCommand(String fp) throws PythonError, IOException, InterruptedException
      Computes the emotions via a Long Short Term Memory neural network and returns the string Pytorch tensor.
      Parameters:
      fp - Path to the mp3 file
      Returns:
      A string of the printed PyTorch tensor of the output of the machine leanring model
      Throws:
      PythonError - If an error occurs within python, python is not installed, or the venv is not initilaized.
      IOException - If reading/writing to CLI fails
      InterruptedException - If underlying Python script fails mid-execution

    • parseOut

      public static EmotionPoint[] parseOut(String s)
      Parses the output of Python to an array of EmotionPoint objects which are typically linked to a song
      Parameters:
      s - The string input which should be taken from runCommand(), a printed Pytorch tensor of dimesnions nx2.
      Returns:
      the array of EmotionPoint objects that was shown in a Torch tensor.

    • clearCache

      public static void clearCache()
      Cleares the cache folder of all downloaded songs, but not the venv or any of the scripts. Deleting the venv must be done manually, but can clear upwards of 2 GB.
